RE: What evidence would convince you of the existence of god? Thanks for this, Phaedrus. You've got me to thinking.
My mind kept refuting answers until it backed itself into a corner. I have but one simple answer:
If God were to make me also God, then....I *might* believe. I can't say for certain, but if I were made omniscient as well, then at least I would know for certain whether the being that just bestowed me with this gift were also the genuine God, what he intends, why, etc. I would also need to be made omnipotent or the deal's off.
He's not the Messiah. He's a very naughty boy! -Brian's mum
