RE: What evidence would convince you of the existence of god? The same evidence of things we already know to exist. God would have to exist then the evidence of that existence could be clearly obtained.
There is no evidence that can be shown for a non existent being
That being would first need to exist then evidence can be presented.
It's like asking what evidence would need to be given for you to believe that you have six arms or that the moon is really made of cheese
